      <title>[Letter] 1847 Sep. 12, Clover Dale, [TN] [to] Mrs. Ann Jane Bell, Charlotte, Dickson Co[unty], Tenn[essee] / Sally [Bell]</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter dated September 12, 1847, from Sally Bell to her sister Ann Jane Bell in Dickson County, TN. Sally discusses their financial situation and expresses thanks for the money both Ann Jane and their brother William has sent to her. She also reports that another William Bell had intended to become the clerk on a ship. Finally, she writes that a crowd of people had cheered on a company of Volunteers in town that day.</abstract>
